Frontier Airlines will charge for hand baggage
Frontier Airlines plans to charge passengers up to $100 for carrying hand baggage aboard their flight.
Frontier Airlines plans to start charging up to $100 for hand baggage and $2 for coffee or soda, although their Wednesday announcement said that passengers could keep the entire can.
The new hand baggage charges extend to the bags in the upper luggage compartments, so the small bags placed under the seat will remain free.
